MYSQL SERVER
https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-mysql-on-ubuntu-18-04
root password: chaeTe4l
login as root: mysql -u root -p
checking mysql service: systemctl status mysql.service

ENVIRONMENT
mysql 5.5
phpmyadmin
node 11

DOCKER
https://docs.docker.com/install/linux/docker-ce/ubuntu/#install-docker-ce-1
(getting started: https://docs.docker.com/get-started/)

- docker cheat sheet: https://docs.docker.com/get-started/#recap-and-cheat-sheet

- GUI for docker management: https://www.portainer.io
sudo docker volume create portainer_data
sudo docker run -d -p 9000:9000 -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock -v portainer_data:/data portainer/portainer

- start mysql server mounting a path to local storage (to make it persistent)
sudo docker run --name spotair_mysql_server -v /path/to/local/persistent_database_dir:/var/lib/mysql -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=motdepasse -d mysql:5.5 

- start phpmyadmin server, link to mysql server and start serving at http://localhost:8080
sudo docker run --name spotair_myadmin -d --link spotair_mysql_server:db -p 8080:80 phpmyadmin/phpmyadmin

- dockerizing a node.js web app
https://nodejs.org/en/docs/guides/nodejs-docker-webapp/

- building your first node application using docker
https://www.javascriptjanuary.com/blog/building-your-first-node-app-using-docker


